This paper deals with a tool for sentence simplification and its application in improving automatic biomedical information extraction. The paper mentions the use of a novel model for sentence simplification that is optimized for processing biomedical scientific literature. This suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), or cybernetics (cs.CY).
